# Microsoft 365 Migration Case Study  
## POP3 to Exchange Online Migration (Multi-Company Environment)

---

## 🧑‍💻 Project Overview

This project involved the migration of legacy POP3 email infrastructure hosted on Xneelo for two business units within the same group:

- Xcelerate Outsourcing  
- Jesmondene  

The environment was modernized by migrating to **Microsoft 365 Exchange Online** to improve security, reliability, scalability, and centralized identity management.

This was a **multi-domain POP3-to-cloud migration** involving manual data extraction, DNS engineering, and Microsoft 365 tenant onboarding.

---

## 🎯 Business Objectives

- Migrate POP3 email systems to Microsoft 365 Exchange Online  
- Consolidate two business units into a unified cloud platform  
- Improve email security and anti-phishing protection  
- Introduce centralized identity management via Entra ID  
- Enable Microsoft Teams and SharePoint collaboration  
- Eliminate dependency on legacy hosting infrastructure  
- Improve scalability for business growth  

---

## 🏗️ Legacy Environment (Xneelo POP3)

### Email Infrastructure
- POP3 email accounts hosted on Xneelo cPanel
- No centralized mailbox storage (PST-based email)
- No identity or directory services
- Device-specific email configuration per user
- Limited security and spam filtering capabilities

### Key Limitations
- No mailbox governance or retention policies  
- No MFA or modern authentication  
- Heavy reliance on Outlook local profiles  
- No centralized backup strategy  
- Fragmented identity across two companies  

---

## ☁️ Target Microsoft 365 Architecture

### Core Services Implemented
- Microsoft Exchange Online  
- Microsoft Entra ID (Azure Active Directory)  
- Microsoft Teams  
- SharePoint Online  
- OneDrive for Business  

### Security Enhancements
- Multi-Factor Authentication (MFA)  
- Conditional Access Policies  
- Exchange Online Protection (EOP)  
- Anti-phishing / Anti-spam policies  
- DKIM, SPF, and DMARC configuration  

---

## 🔧 Migration Strategy

### 1. Environment Assessment
- Audited POP3 mailboxes across both companies  
- Identified PST-based email storage usage  
- Manually mapped users (no directory sync available)  
- Reviewed DNS records in Xneelo  

---

### 2. Microsoft 365 Tenant Setup
- Created Microsoft 365 tenant  
- Added and verified both domains  
- Configured Exchange Online mail flow  
- Created users and security groups in Entra ID  

---

### 3. DNS Cutover & Mail Flow
- Migrated MX records to Microsoft 365 (EOP)  
- Configured SPF records for domain protection  
- Enabled DKIM signing  
- Implemented DMARC policy for reporting and enforcement  

---

### 4. POP3 Data Migration (Manual Method)

Due to POP3 limitations, migration was executed manually:

- Exported mailbox data via Outlook PST files  
- Cleaned and validated PST structures per user  
- Imported PSTs into Exchange Online mailboxes  
- Verified folder structure and email integrity  

---

### 5. Client Reconfiguration
- Reconfigured Outlook from POP3 to Exchange Online  
- Migrated mobile devices to Exchange ActiveSync  
- Disabled legacy POP3 authentication  
- Standardized SMTP authentication via Microsoft 365  

---

## 🔐 Security Improvements

- Eliminated insecure POP3 authentication  
- Enabled MFA across all users  
- Implemented Conditional Access policies  
- Strengthened email security posture  
- Removed legacy hosting exposure  

---

## 📡 DNS & Identity Engineering

- Managed DNS cutover and propagation timing  
- Executed staged migration to avoid downtime  
- Configured:
  - SPF (Sender Policy Framework)  
  - DKIM (DomainKeys Identified Mail)  
  - DMARC (Email authentication & reporting)  

---

## ⚠️ Challenges & Constraints

### 1. Legacy POP3 System
No native migration path — required full manual PST handling.

### 2. No Central Identity
No Active Directory or synchronization required manual user mapping.

### 3. DNS Propagation Delays
Cutover timing depended on external DNS propagation windows.

### 4. End-User Dependency
Users relied on POP3 Outlook profiles requiring full reconfiguration.

### 5. Data Integrity Risks
Manual PST migration required validation to prevent duplication or corruption.

